China says cancer-causing red dye Sudan I found in Heinz products The red dye Sudan I has been found in a pepper sauce made by the Heinz Meiweiyuan Food Co. based in Guangzhou.
Sudan-I is a red dye used for coloring solvents, oils, waxes, petrol and shoe and floor polishes.
According to the China's General Administration for Industry and Commerce, food containing Sudan I had passed into China's municipalities, provinces and autonomous regions including Beijing and Shanghai.
All products and materials will undergo spot checks and suppliers have also been told to tighten supervision of their products.
